descriptions.text: Produces a bank iban number.
Specifies what country prefix is used to generate the iban code. Providing ‘nil` will use a random country.

Calculates the mandatory checksum in 3rd and 4th characters in IBAN format source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Bank_Account_Number#Generating_IBAN_check_digits.

Calculates the mandatory checksum in 3rd and 4th characters in IBAN format source: en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Bank_Account_Number#Generating_IBAN_check_digits

implementations.data:
(country_code, account)
				# Converts letters to numbers according the iban rules, A=10..Z=35
				account_to_number = "#{account}#{country_code}00".upcase.chars.map do |d|
				d =~ /[A-Z]/ ? (d.ord - 55).to_s : d
				end.join.to_i

				# This is the correct answer to (iban_to_num + checksum) % 97 == 1
				checksum = 98 - (account_to_number % 97)

				# Use leftpad to make the size always to 2
				checksum.to_s.rjust(2, '0')
